        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 31. Sonarina tamilensis Taylor and Di Martino, holotype, NHMUK BZ7849; Cretaceous, late Campanian or early Maastrichtian, Kallankurichchi Limestone No. 3mine Trichinopoly District, Tamil Nadu, India; (a) autozooids and an avicularium (arrowed) at a row bifurcation; (b) ovicellate autozooid; (c) avicularium with rostrum touching the distal end of an autozooidal opesia. Scale bars = 200 µm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4747216/files/figure.png" .

